  "prompt": "How can I learn math from zero?",
  "response": "Learning math from scratch can be approached systematically:\n\n1. Basic Foundation\n- Start with basic arithmetic\n- Learn addition, subtraction, multiplication, division\n- Practice mental math\n- Use educational websites like Khan Academy\n\n2. Algebra\n- Learn variables and equations\n- Practice solving simple algebraic problems\n- Understand basic algebraic manipulation\n\n3. Geometry\n- Learn basic shapes and their properties\n- Understand angles, measurements\n- Study geometric proofs\n\n4. Online Resources\n- Khan Academy (free comprehensive math courses)\n- Coursera\n- YouTube educational channels\n- Math learning websites\n\n5. Learning Strategies\n- Start with fundamentals\n- Practice consistently\n- Use workbooks and practice problems\n- Don't rush, build understanding gradually\n- Use visual learning tools\n- Solve problems step-by-step\n\n6. Additional Tools\n- Math learning apps\n- Online tutoring\n- Math textbooks\n- Interactive learning platforms\n\n7. Advanced Steps\n- Trigonometry\n- Calculus\n- Linear algebra\n- Statistics\n\n8. Tips\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Embrace mistakes as learning opportunities\n- Break complex problems into smaller steps\n- Stay motivated\n- Develop a growth mindset\n\nConsistent practice and a structured approach are key to learning math effectively.",
